🚢 Port Binding in Docker
1️⃣ First Understand This Clearly

When you create a Docker container:

It runs in its own network namespace
It has its own IP address
It has its own ports
It has its own filesystem

👉 Yes, filesystem is isolated.
👉 And network (including ports) is also isolated.

🔥 Key Point
A container can expose a port internally,
but that port is NOT accessible from your host machine unless you bind it.

What this means:
Host Machine	Docker Container
localhost:8080	container:80

Now:
You open browser → http://localhost:8080
Docker forwards request → container port 80
📦 Visual Understanding
Host Machine
-------------------------
localhost:8080
        │
        ▼
Docker Port Mapping
        │
        ▼
Container
-------------------------
